---
{% if is_teapot %}
    <div class="hero">
        <h1>ü´ñ I'm a Teapot! ü´ñ</h1>
        <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            Welcome! Status <span class="highlight">418 I'm a teapot</span> is a
            real HTTP status code that exists to declare one simple truth:
            teapots don't brew coffee.
        </p>
        <p>
            Born from an April Fools' joke in 1998, this status code somehow
            stuck around and became a quirky part of web development lore. Here
            we'll look at its history, explore the HTTP protocol bits that make
            it work, and see why it's still hanging around today.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-style: italic; opacity: 0.9;">
            Any attempt to brew coffee with a teapot should result in the error
            code <span class="highlight">"418 I'm a teapot"</span>. The
            resulting entity body MAY be short and stout.
        </p>
    </div>
{% endif %}
{% match error_message %}
    {% when Some(msg) %}
        <!-- Error message content: {{ msg }} -->
        <div class="error-box">
            <div {% match error_message %}{% when Some(m) %}data-has-error="true"{% when None %}data-has-error="false"{% endmatch %}>
                ‚ö†Ô∏è {{ msg }}
            </div>
        </div>
    {% when None %}
{% endmatch %}
<section id="statistics" class="section" {% let total_brews = brew_attempts + successful_teas %}>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.05rem; color: #666;">
        But don't just take our word for it‚Äîlet the numbers tell the story of
        our unwavering commitment to tea.
    </p>
    <h2>Our Track Record</h2>
    <!-- Brew attempts: {{ brew_attempts }}, Successful teas: {{ successful_teas }} -->
    <div class="stats-container">
        {% for stat_index in 0..2 %}
            <div class="stat-box">
                {% if stat_index == 0 %}
                    <div class="stat-number">{{ brew_attempts }}</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Brew Attempts</div>
                {% elif stat_index == 1 %}
                    <div class="stat-number">{{ successful_teas }}</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Successful Teas</div>
                {% endif %}
            </div>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% let success_rate = successful_teas * 100 / total_brews %}
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.2rem;">
        Tea Success Rate: <strong>{{ success_rate }}%</strong> | Coffee Success
        Rate: <strong>0%</strong> (as it should be!)
    </p>
</section>
<!-- Teapot types section -->
<section id="teapots" class="section">
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: #666;">
        Of course, not all teapots are created equal. Let's meet some of the
        distinguished vessels that proudly uphold the 418 standard.
    </p>
    <h2>Distinguished Teapot Types</h2>
    <div class="teapot-grid" {% for idx in 0..teapot_types.len() %}data-teapot-{{ idx }}="loaded" {% endfor %}>
        {% for teapot in teapot_types %}
            {% if !teapot.can_brew_coffee %}
                <div class="teapot-card {% if is_teapot %}authentic{% endif %}">
                    <div class="teapot-emoji">{{ teapot.emoji }}</div>
                    <div class="teapot-name">{{ teapot.name }}</div>
                    <div class="teapot-origin">Origin: {{ teapot.origin }}</div>
                    <span class="badge badge-incompatible">
                        ‚úì Coffee Incompatible
                    </span>
                </div>
            {% else %}
                <div class="teapot-card">
                    <div class="teapot-emoji">{{ teapot.emoji }}</div>
                    <div class="teapot-name">{{ teapot.name }}</div>
                    <div class="teapot-origin">Origin: {{ teapot.origin }}</div>
                    <span class="badge badge-imposter">
                        ‚ö†Ô∏è Not a Real Teapot
                    </span>
                </div>
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>
<!-- Fun Facts section -->
<section id="facts" class="section">
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: #666;">
        Beyond the teapots themselves, the 418 status code has a rich and
        entertaining backstory worth exploring.
    </p>
    <h2>Fun Facts About HTTP 418</h2>
    <div class="facts-list">
        {% if show_history %}
            {% for fact in fun_facts %}
                <div class="fact-item">ü´ñ {{ fact }}</div>
            {% endfor %}
        {% endif %}
    </div>
</section>
